ğŸ“˜ Day Blog: Understanding Props in React
ğŸ“Œ What are Props in React?

Props (short for properties) are used to pass data from one component to another.
Props make components reusable and dynamic.

ğŸ‘‰ Props are read-only (we cannot change them inside the child component).

ğŸ”¹ Props in Functional Components

In a functional component, props are received as a parameter.

âœ… Example 1: Simple Props with Function Component
Parent Component
function App() {
  return (
    <div>
      <Student name="Rahul" course="MCA" />
    </div>
  );
}

Child Component
function Student(props) {
  return (
    <div>
      <h2>Name: {props.name}</h2>
      <p>Course: {props.course}</p>
    </div>
  );
}

ğŸ“ Explanation:

App is the parent component

Student is the child component

Data (name, course) is passed as props

We access props using props.propertyName

âœ… Example 2: Props using Destructuring (Best Practice)
function Student({ name, course }) {
  return (
    <div>
      <h2>Name: {name}</h2>
      <p>Course: {course}</p>
    </div>
  );
}


âœ” Cleaner
âœ” Easy to read
âœ” Mostly used in real projects

ğŸ”¹ Props in Class Components

In class components, props are accessed using this.props.

âœ… Example: Props with Class Component
Parent Component
function App() {
  return (
    <div>
      <Teacher subject="React" experience="3 Years" />
    </div>
  );
}

Child Component
import React, { Component } from "react";

class Teacher extends Component {
  render() {
    return (
      <div>
        <h2>Subject: {this.props.subject}</h2>
        <p>Experience: {this.props.experience}</p>
      </div>
    );
  }
}

export default Teacher;

ğŸ“ Explanation:

In class components, we must use this.props

Props work the same way as function components

Only the syntax is different

ğŸ”‘ Key Points to Remember

Props are used to send data from parent to child

Props are immutable (read-only)

Functional Component â†’ props or destructuring

Class Component â†’ this.props

Props help in reusability of components

ğŸ’¡ Real-Life Example

Think of props like:

ğŸ“¦ Gift from parent to child
Child can use the gift but cannot change it ğŸ

âœ… Conclusion

Props are one of the most important concepts in React.
Understanding props clearly helps you build dynamic, reusable, and clean components.

